": "", "problem_statement": "[REQUEST] Small Type Icons\nNot really needed but definitely a quality of life improval.\n", "hints_text": "Can you please give examples?\nI imagined something like this \n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93634280-85bf-4107-847f-792a650e3ff5)\nIn addition to the icons with text\nWe could serve them through this endpoint `https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/type/{id or name}/` we can divide the current type icons to `badges/` (symbol + text) and `icons/` (for just symbols) and then update the api to serve both right here https://github.com/PokeAPI/pokeapi/blob/7ed7e9d7d13eba25327dfd9395e00d42bd54f337/data/v2/build.py#L660-L664 something like this\n```py\nsprites[generation][game] = {\n                    \"name_icon\": file_path_or_none(\n                        f\"types/{generation}/{game}/badges/{info[0]}.png\"\n                    ),\n                    \"icon\": file_path_or_none(\n                       f\"types/{generation}/{game}/icons/{info[0]}.png\"\n                    ),\n                }\n```\n@DerCooleJustin feel free to make a pr if you can \nHi @FallenDeity,\nthanks for the response! I actually already forgot about this issue, but this would make a lot of sense.\nI'm not really invested into the codebase for the api, but I can try to find some icons (or edit them myself) and make a PR to this repo.\nI may also clone the data repo and check if everything builds with the change you suggested, and try fixing any bugs this might create, but don't expect too much from me over there.\nYeah that sounds good too, any contribution counts :) if its added to the sprites repo I can make a pr in the api repo\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Can you please give examples?\nI imagined something like this \n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93634280-85bf-4107-847f-792a650e3ff5)\nIn addition to the icons with text\nWe could serve them through this endpoint `https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/type/{id or name}/` we can divide the current type icons to `badges/` (symbol + text) and `icons/` (for just symbols) and then update the api to serve both right here https://github.com/PokeAPI/pokeapi/blob/7ed7e9d7d13eba25327dfd9395e00d42bd54f337/data/v2/build.py#L660-L664 something like this\n```py\nsprites[generation][game] = {\n                    \"name_icon\": file_path_or_none(\n                        f\"types/{generation}/{game}/badges/{info[0]}.png\"\n                    ),\n                    \"icon\": file_path_or_none(\n                       f\"types/{generation}/{game}/icons/{info[0]}.png\"\n                    ),\n                }\n```\n@DerCooleJustin feel free to make a pr if you can \nHi @FallenDeity,\nthanks for the response! I actually already forgot about this issue, but this would make a lot of sense.\nI'm not really invested into the codebase for the api, but I can try to find some icons (or edit them myself) and make a PR to this repo.\nI may also clone the data repo and check if everything builds with the change you suggested, and try fixing any bugs this might create, but don't expect too much from me over there.\nYeah that sounds good too, any contribution counts :) if its added to the sprites repo I can make a pr in the api repo\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/90085d6d621208d32a267c6793e2a6f6a679cb58", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/39146a1b84e7a48102465b5f82039225ffb1c128", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/e6c112b70fbc06a423d0df5b5586ccfdbc75d320", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/ea8af1401e5062d2768252811fece1078c8969e3", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/ce8938376df94663222f871d62a89a2a4ebd67c3", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/73ad0d009e79d16e8d581618a91ea2e70b88dc97", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/3831906f0c671a0485f46f632b81d98d850d8a42", "https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/9ada2df03c75521603bc10565df871be74a3ec33"], "created_at": "2026-02-28T21:07:20Z"}
