l/18.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/18.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/2.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/2.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/2.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/2.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/3.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/3.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/3.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/3.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/4.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/4.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/4.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/4.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/5.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/5.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/5.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/5.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/6.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/6.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/6.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/6.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/7.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/7.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/7.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/7.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/8.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/8.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/8.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/8.png\ndiff --git a/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/9.png b/sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/9.png\nsimilarity index 100%\nrename from sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl/small/9.png\nrename to sprites/types/generation-viii/brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl/small/9.png\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Different names for BDSP in sprites and api repos\n> Hey just a quick note the `brilliant-diamond-...` folder in gen 8 is named `brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl` in this repo while the game is named `brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl`.\n> \n> <img width=\"487\" height=\"96\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7233bd28-b51d-448d-86e4-ad4ba0d2b8c5\" />\n> \n> I think this slipped by here https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/pull/139/changes can we you rename that folder to `brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl`\n\n_Originally posted by @FallenDeity in https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/issues/199#issuecomment-4016393776_\n            \n===\n\nMaking this a new issue for the reason stated here https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/pull/199#issuecomment-4016456504\n", "hints_text": "Hi! Thanks for the catch. World you be able to fix the issue on your own? \nI definitely am able to fix, but i thought this might deserve a short discussion. It's been like this for 1.5yrs, and might break some older downloaders who don't bother using actual PokeAPI data and instead download directly from GH using hardcoded paths.\nI know this an *extreme* edge case, but do we just ignore it or do we somehow respect it?\nIf this isn't important to you, i will link a quick pr.\nI do see some direct consumption from sprites repo https://github.com/search?q=brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl&type=code renaming it is definitely required either from api side or sprite side (sprite side seems more apt). But maybe we can leave that folder for backwards compatibility and mark it deprecated and remove it in one if the future prs so it doesn't suddenly cause impact. Maybe also add a note.\n\ncc: @Naramsim what are your thoughts on this\nHi, I think we can go with renaming the `brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl` folder to `brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl`, then regenerate the API and we should have the right link. The API isn't serving them and that matters the most over people using hardcoded paths. \n\nWe could use the `-and-` name in the function that reads the images over at pokeapi but it's also a matter of consistency. \n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi! Thanks for the catch. World you be able to fix the issue on your own? \nI definitely am able to fix, but i thought this might deserve a short discussion. It's been like this for 1.5yrs, and might break some older downloaders who don't bother using actual PokeAPI data and instead download directly from GH using hardcoded paths.\nI know this an *extreme* edge case, but do we just ignore it or do we somehow respect it?\nIf this isn't important to you, i will link a quick pr.\nI do see some direct consumption from sprites repo https://github.com/search?q=brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl&type=code renaming it is definitely required either from api side or sprite side (sprite side seems more apt). But maybe we can leave that folder for backwards compatibility and mark it deprecated and remove it in one if the future prs so it doesn't suddenly cause impact. Maybe also add a note.\n\ncc: @Naramsim what are your thoughts on this\nHi, I think we can go with renaming the `brilliant-diamond-and-shining-pearl` folder to `brilliant-diamond-shining-pearl`, then regenerate the API and we should have the right link. The API isn't serving them and that matters the most over people using hardcoded paths. \n\nWe could use the `-and-` name in the function that reads the images over at pokeapi but it's also a matter of consistency. \n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/8774627eb13df5983e586d252711292f0c8de102"], "created_at": "2026-03-12T19:27:55Z"}
{"repo": "PokeAPI/sprites", "pull_number": 209, "instance_id": "PokeAPI__sprites-209", "issue_numbers": [208], "base_commit": "d8eba5657870d202c17905a3d9c412a758164b66", "patch": "diff --git a/sprites/badges/70.png b/sprites/badges/70.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..0eac52ffa4\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/70.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/71.png b/sprites/badges/71.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..3a72cce8a5\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/71.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/72.png b/sprites/badges/72.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..75ba3458f7\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/72.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/73.png b/sprites/badges/73.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..4a740af8fd\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/73.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/74.png b/sprites/badges/74.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..368ff5e053\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/74.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/75.png b/sprites/badges/75.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..cd7cbb6154\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/75.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/76.png b/sprites/badges/76.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..ba2b3cba6d\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/76.png differ\ndiff --git a/sprites/badges/77.png b/sprites/badges/77.png\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..5039260ad8\nBinary files /dev/null and b/sprites/badges/77.png differ\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Paldea Badges\nI'm not sure how to contribute here so let me ask, may I add the Paldea badges here?\n\nI've been using this repository's badges on a game I created, and needed the gen 9 now.\n\nIs there any rule to it? \n\nBy the way, where in the API can I view the badges?\n", "hints_text": "Badges aren't yet part of the API. \n\nFeel free to add the images to the right folder of the sprites repository by opening a PR. Then we will review your contribution \n\nTry to find official images. \n\n", "all_hints_text": "Badges aren't yet part of the API. \n\nFeel free to add the images to the right folder of the sprites repository by opening a PR. Then we will review your contribution \n\nTry to find official images. \nAlright done on Pull Request #209 \n\nI've used a different account there, but it's still me\nI see some other badges are low quality or have a white contour. Would you be able to fix those?\nOh wow, it was already merged, thanks!\n\nAbout the images, the main problem is we need data mining from the game, because these images are quite rare.\n\nI mean, I could find on the internet better images, for example Bulbapedia uses them on their articles, but it's not official\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/commit/0c1dd748cdc48cde2d47f4241f62ed4f4a200467"], "created_at": "2026-03-15T21:59:00Z"}
